column5: Just sharing a couple nuice pictures from this weekend.. water was very clear, tough day but managed a couple..    biggest of the day. picture doesnt do it justice.. around 10 lbs..
Indeed...
Definately a Banner Day of Epic proportions!!!
"STELLAR"
Great looking fish that, i'm gonna have to try this 'steelheading' lark one day.
Dobee, love the handles on your pin   Did they come with it or were they something you added later?
thanks bill..that was the first fish i got on my new 13' rainshadow xst & islander reel.. very nice rod, the cork handles are a custom jobby.
totally EPIC report!
Epically banner pics. Thx for sharin.
SUPAKALIFRAGILISTIC-EPIC-ALYDOSIOUS!!  wuwuuuutt!
lol. Epic indeed
The pics are epic . Well the Islander has a 4.5" diameter right? juxtaposed, it looks small against that fish. Well done!  thanks for sharing.  p.-
Big river steelhead, now that's the right way to break in a new stick! (First pic is very cool btw)
Whoa you caught a fish ! Ha ha good stuff man! Are you fishing saturday?
thanks for the comments..  i cant fish the derby on saturday.. my nephew won his semi final game yesterday and the championship game is saturday at 12:30... good luck though..
SIC first pic and a nice clean freshy on the second one ... I have to come down and fish the big riva sometime soon
Great report and pics dobee  Beautiful steel!! congratulations and thanks for sharing Leechman
UUUBBER!!!!!
sweet pics dude
Beautiful pics Dobee.  Love the scenery.  Can't think of a better way to break in the new stick.  Congrats
nice! You caught up my way?  That should have tested the new gear well.
